			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I posted this in it's own thread, but it didn't get much attention...
<br />

<br />
I think this would be a viable solution to the problem of low skill caps:
<br />

<br />
I was thinking a new AA that could be included which many beastlords have asked for would be something like: 
<br />

<br />
Weapon Mastery AA 
<br />

<br />
There would be 3 tiers for this AA. You would first have to choose a weapon skill (1hb, 2hb or 1hp) to raise over 225. With the first Weapon Mastery AA you would be able to raise your skill to 232. Next AA would allow you to raise your selected weapon mastery to 242, or allow you to raise another skill to 232. The third would allow you to hit the cap at 252 if you chose to stick with only one weapon mastery or raise a 3rd weapon skill, or progress another already chosen skill. 
<br />

<br />
Essentially you could raise the cap on all your weapon skills to 232, or raise the cap on one of your weapon skills to 252, or have one skill raised to 242, and one skill raised to 232. 
<br />

<br />
I think this would take care of a lot of gripes about BST with high end 2hb, 1hb or 1hp weapons, and are stuck with a lower skill cap. Each tier would be worth quite a few AA as it could be a signifigant jump in our dps. I'm thinking around 9-12AA per weapon mastery tier.<br />_________________<br /><center><b>Atropine "Sulfate" Invictus</b> </center><center>Up and coming Beastlord</center><center> <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=798105> Gear </a> </center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
