		<td class="row2" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
			<tr>
				<td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=106272&amp;sid=dd1b52f8542555a6a180edc906f58726#106272"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Tue Dec 09, 2003 5:40 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
				<td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=106272&amp;sid=dd1b52f8542555a6a180edc906f58726"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I never liked ideas that are 'balanced' because they are 'expensive' or have 'penalties'
<br />

<br />
Why?  Because sooner than you think, people will have them, and work out how to get all the advantages without the penalties really mattering.
<br />

<br />
Although in this case, the increase in skill cap from your weapon mastery will not be that huge a change in DPS - and thus there isnt actually a need to 'balance' them through expense.
<br />

<br />
But there is still the need for balance through comparison to other classes.
<br />

<br />
Is it fair to class balance?  BL are already quite capable - our pretty much certain access to some type of slow, haste, and attack buff means even though a monk owns us in defence and offence skills, on a one to one comparison, we will tank better (slow makes more difference than any amount of defence skill) and still be relatively close on melee (double attack is like 70pct extra stackable haste, hard to top that)
<br />

<br />
But whats that?  A shammie makes all that beast stuff irrelevant?  Not so much as you think.  We got a few tricks the shammies dont, and we can use our slow with relative impunity knowing that drawing early agro isnt really a problem.  The monk still has to either tank the mob unslowed for a bit, or let the shaman tank initially (and 75% slow lets the shaman tank a (slowed) mob better than a monk (against unslowed) )
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
The problem I see with so many neato class ideas is they identify a deficiency in a class (this thread is about our lower weapon skills) and seek to add an improvement, trying to engineer in balance in some way.  They seldom look at deficiencies and strengths in a class compared to those in other classes to identify an imbalance, then add an improvement to correct an inbalance (which then doesnt need an engineered balance, because by its nature, it is moving things away from an unbalanced state to a balanced state)
<br />

<br />

<br />
Woo - wrote more than I thought I would.  Sigh - I find myself invariably poo pooing 'balance' suggestions because (as I see them) they are usually not balanceing actions at all.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Anyway - weapon mastery, and skill caps in general - these are good points for EXPANSION material - maybe if levels go from 66-70 there needs to be thought about these ideas.  But balance?  no - I think BL are on the level as is.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Disclaimer - I would love to have skill caps in all skills at 250.  I would love to have double attack up to 250.  I would love to have triple attack AAs.  I would love to have innate crits with HTH.  I would love to have innate crits and deadly strikes with HTH when we strike from behind (advantage here is it doesnt give us any solo power).  I would love to have fire based or poison based nukes.  I would love to have HoT spells for pet.  I would love to have cani.  I would love to have Pet uberification buff that lasts 2 minues with 45 min rebuff.  I would love to have pet swarm AA.  And so on and so on and so on.  Yet - I WILL argue against any of these things if they get put up as 'balancing' ideas unless someone can actually demonstrated that BL are unbalanced in a negative way against the other classes in the game.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
