			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Zone ins are wither safe - in which case there is no problem - or not safe.
<br />

<br />
Mages, SKs, Necros, BL, Chanters with charmed pets, Druids with charmed pets, Shammies, rangers that like wolf form, rogues that are relying on hide/sneak - loads of stuff that doesnt zone - 8 classes out of 15 (or how ever many - I lost count.)
<br />

<br />
So - maybe you are right - there is a problem with zoning in.  I disagree - zones that are not safe by design are known and people deal with it, zones that are not safe by train will kill anyone - BoT is a great example of that.
<br />

<br />
Wizzies - they got nothing particular that they loose on zoning.
<br />

<br />
Wizzie zones into a not safe zone - gets bashed and stunned, gang attacked, and dead - BL gets bashed and stunned, pops defensive /disc, and superior avoidance skills has a far greater likelyhood of survival than the wizard.
<br />

<br />
Warriors cant even invis themselves without relying on items or potions.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Seems to me that BL are actually way ahead on this.  Once again its a situation that was plucked out as an example, without considering the implications across the classes as a whole.  You cant balance anything by looking at only one side of the scale (well, unless you can also prove that a change to one side has the equal and opposite affect on the other side, such as a real lever scale balance - so really this was a terrible analargy to use - EQ class balance is way more comvoluted than a balance scale)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
